HEADWORD: Eparchy
<hw>Ep"arch*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ the post or
office of an <?/.]</ety> <def>A province, prefecture, or territory,
under the jurisdiction of an eparch or governor; esp., in modern Greece,
one of the larger subdivisions of a monarchy or province of the kingdom;
in Russia, a diocese or archdiocese.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

